cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 90 miles W of Camagüey, Cuba and 300 miles S of Miami, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving northeast across central Cuba, then turning north-northwest into the Florida Straits and toward the Florida Keys before bending westward over the southeastern Gulf of Mexico
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: near or over the Florida Keys

weather_observation.watch_coast: Storm-surge and hurricane watches in effect from Golden Beach FL to Bonita Beach FL including the Florida Keys and Biscayne Bay
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical-storm warnings for much of south-central Cuba, the north-western Bahamas, the Florida Keys and the southern Florida peninsula
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central Cuba, north-western Bahamas, South Florida including the Keys, and eventually the eastern Gulf Coast of Florida
weather_observation.wind: Only a very small (≤3%) chance of tropical-storm-force winds late in the 5-day period; otherwise normal breezes
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the South Carolina coast
weather_observation.rainfall: No heavy rainfall associated with Eta is expected at the port during the forecast window
